The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for robotics, specifically in the context of imitation learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and dropout, which are common techniques in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), respectively.
